WEBVTT

00:01.277 --> 00:02.657
- Previously
on "The Rookie"...

00:02.692 --> 00:03.658
- Bailey.
- Jason.

00:03.693 --> 00:05.005
- Who are you?

00:05.039 --> 00:06.316
- I'm John Nolan,
her boyfriend.

00:06.351 --> 00:07.731
And you are?
- Her husband.

00:07.766 --> 00:10.424
- Jason is behind bars
for eight years.

00:10.458 --> 00:11.804
- Gundo's expecting me.

00:11.839 --> 00:13.289
A hit man came after me.

00:13.323 --> 00:15.429
I need to know who sent him.

00:15.463 --> 00:17.189
- Batista needs child care.

00:17.224 --> 00:19.019
And his former nanny...
- Our current nanny.

00:19.053 --> 00:20.813
- Is willing to
sing your praises.

00:20.848 --> 00:22.436
- I'm here to see
Christian Batista.

00:22.470 --> 00:23.644
I have an appointment.

00:23.678 --> 00:25.094
- If you're here
for the hot prison goss,

00:25.128 --> 00:26.336
it's going to cost you.

00:26.371 --> 00:29.098
- Eric Ramsey
is the man after me.

00:29.132 --> 00:31.238
- You need to take him out.
- That's where you come in.

00:31.272 --> 00:33.274
- Kelso.
He's a dangerous man.

00:33.309 --> 00:35.207
- He was also
Ramsey's right hand.

00:35.242 --> 00:36.933
- I want you to help
me break out of prison.

00:36.967 --> 00:38.072
- Deal.

00:38.107 --> 00:39.901
- Who was
the investigating officer?

00:39.936 --> 00:41.489
- Pearson.
- If he gives me up,

00:41.524 --> 00:44.251
the recordings from your
sessions go straight to IA.

00:45.390 --> 00:47.461
- It's a simple question.

00:47.495 --> 00:49.808
Did they flip
the shrink or not?

00:49.842 --> 00:51.154
You're my lawyer.

00:51.189 --> 00:53.501
You're supposed to know
these things.

00:55.641 --> 00:57.712
Morning.

00:59.438 --> 01:02.441
No. No.
That's not right.

01:02.476 --> 01:04.547
You tell them--
[muffled gunshot]

01:04.581 --> 01:06.652
[dramatic music]

01:06.687 --> 01:09.138
[muffled gunshot,
engine revving]

01:09.172 --> 01:16.006
♪

01:18.906 --> 01:20.942
[objects clatter]

01:22.634 --> 01:25.395
[dog whimpers]

01:25.430 --> 01:32.092
♪

01:33.990 --> 01:36.303
[truck squeals, hisses]

01:36.337 --> 01:43.378
♪

01:55.356 --> 01:57.082
- Good morning.
- Hi.

01:57.116 --> 01:58.842
- I was waiting
for you to wake up

01:58.877 --> 02:00.982
but then I'm going to have to
go pretty soon, so I had to...

02:01.017 --> 02:02.846
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

02:02.881 --> 02:06.160
I have just been doing
a lot of thinking.

02:06.195 --> 02:09.267
And I know what you said about
not being willing to go through

02:09.300 --> 02:11.061
with the whole IVF routine,

02:11.096 --> 02:13.685
and I completely
support you on that,

02:13.719 --> 02:16.757
but I have been watching you
these past few days.

02:16.791 --> 02:20.278
And you've been putting
on a very brave face,

02:20.312 --> 02:21.762
but you are sad.

02:21.796 --> 02:25.731
And I am tasked with your
happiness--with our happiness.

02:25.766 --> 02:29.459
And I think that there is
a path that is still open to us

02:29.494 --> 02:31.565
that will bring
a child into our home

02:31.599 --> 02:34.361
and bring us that happiness.

02:34.395 --> 02:36.363
And...

02:36.397 --> 02:38.123
I think we should adopt.

02:39.642 --> 02:41.230
- "Adopt"?
- Yes.

02:41.264 --> 02:45.199
There are so many kids
out there who need a good home

02:45.234 --> 02:47.236
and a loving family.

02:47.270 --> 02:49.721
And, Bailey, that's us.

02:50.860 --> 02:52.275
So what do you think?

02:52.310 --> 02:56.210
- I-I think it's
a beautiful idea.

02:56.245 --> 02:58.316
Also a lot to think about.
- Of course.

02:58.350 --> 03:01.319
And I've done a little bit
of light research.

03:01.353 --> 03:03.321
There's an email waiting
for you in your inbox.

03:03.355 --> 03:06.220
Peruse it as you will
through your morning coffee

03:06.255 --> 03:09.085
and your breakfast
and probably lunch.

03:09.119 --> 03:11.225
I said "light research."
That was the wrong adjective.

03:11.260 --> 03:13.158
It was really, honestly,
pretty extensive.

03:13.193 --> 03:15.643
- [chuckles]
I got it.

03:15.678 --> 03:18.819
Any chance you're going to be
home tonight so we can discuss?

03:18.853 --> 03:21.684
- Uh, that much I don't know.

03:21.718 --> 03:23.962
Things are pretty crazy
at the station right now.

03:23.996 --> 03:25.860
I mean, we still
don't know how many cops

03:25.895 --> 03:28.656
Blair London has compromised
or who's controlling her.

03:28.691 --> 03:30.727
[cell phone rings]

03:30.762 --> 03:32.833
Sorry.

03:32.867 --> 03:34.041
It's Grey.

03:34.075 --> 03:36.423
Yes, sir.
What's going on?

03:36.457 --> 03:39.598
- We're operating
under the radar for now.

03:39.633 --> 03:41.082
- There's still
too many unknowns,

03:41.117 --> 03:42.567
including how deep
the conspiracy runs.

03:42.601 --> 03:44.500
So we are setting up
a secret war room

03:44.534 --> 03:46.466
at the station
using only officers

03:46.502 --> 03:48.124
that we know we can trust.

03:48.158 --> 03:50.471
You up to speed on Pearson?
- No. What happened?

03:50.506 --> 03:53.060
- He's gone. Wife said he took
the garbage to the curb,

03:53.094 --> 03:54.648
never came back.
- Do we think he's running?

03:54.682 --> 03:56.857
- I think he's dead
or on his way there.

03:56.891 --> 03:58.962
- Okay.
Well, how can the FBI help out?

03:58.997 --> 04:01.241
- Simple--we don't know who we
can trust in our own house,

04:01.275 --> 04:03.139
which means we need
your resources

04:03.173 --> 04:05.348
to keep our investigation
under the radar.

04:05.383 --> 04:07.419
- Of course.
What's your path to clarity

04:07.454 --> 04:09.525
as to who's been compromised?
- That would be Blair London.

04:09.559 --> 04:11.699
She's the department shrink
who's been turning cops

04:11.734 --> 04:13.908
and selling police intel
to an unknown number

04:13.943 --> 04:15.289
of criminal organizations.

04:15.324 --> 04:17.636
- And where is this
Blair London now?

04:17.671 --> 04:19.914
- I'm here to tell you
that this deal is the best shot

04:19.949 --> 04:21.329
your client has for a future,

04:21.363 --> 04:23.193
and that future will definitely
involve prison time--

04:23.228 --> 04:24.505
at least three to five years.

04:24.540 --> 04:27.094
- No.
No, I can't go to prison.

04:27.128 --> 04:29.096
I need total immunity.
- That's not going to happen.

04:29.130 --> 04:30.304
You were directly responsible

04:30.339 --> 04:31.788
for a deadly attack
on police officers.

04:31.823 --> 04:33.721
You would have to give us
the equivalent

04:33.756 --> 04:36.724
of Hannibal Lecter or
Pablo Escobar to skate on that.

04:36.759 --> 04:38.933
So take the morning,

04:38.968 --> 04:41.177
but I'm going to need a "yes"
or "no" on this deal

04:41.211 --> 04:42.592
by nightfall.

04:44.767 --> 04:46.320
- Wesley isn't lying.

04:46.355 --> 04:49.254
Three to five is a solid deal
given your criminal liability.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.497
- This is a nightmare.

04:50.531 --> 04:52.706
- Unfortunately,
it's very real.

04:52.740 --> 04:56.503
And you need to accept the fact
that judgment day is here.

05:01.093 --> 05:04.787
[suspenseful music]

05:04.821 --> 05:07.997
[car door closes]

05:08.031 --> 05:10.931
[engines turning over]

05:10.965 --> 05:17.903
♪

05:17.938 --> 05:20.734
[line trilling]

05:20.768 --> 05:21.942
- The shrink is flipping.

05:21.976 --> 05:23.771
She just met with
an ADA at his house,

05:23.806 --> 05:26.118
and she's got a surveillance
team watching her.

05:26.153 --> 05:28.673
Making a play will be risky.

05:28.707 --> 05:31.986
Understood.

05:32.021 --> 05:35.645
We need to take
the shrink off the field.

05:35.680 --> 05:39.269
I know,
but the payday is immense.

05:39.304 --> 05:41.651
I know we can't spend it
if we're dead or in prison,

05:41.686 --> 05:43.584
but we're smart, we're quick,

05:43.619 --> 05:46.898
and we're destined
for a long life of badassery,

05:46.932 --> 05:48.313
so cowboy up.

05:48.348 --> 05:50.142
Let's go get her.

05:50.177 --> 05:54.146
[engine turning over]

05:57.046 --> 05:58.634
- You could at least
pretend to help me.

05:58.668 --> 06:00.981
- I'm here in more
of an oversight capacity.

06:01.015 --> 06:02.396
- [scoffs]
Yeah.

06:02.431 --> 06:04.191
- Smitty,
get your ass into gear.

06:04.225 --> 06:05.882
- Yes, ma'am.
- How's it going?

06:05.917 --> 06:07.919
- I really wish there were
more cops on the no column.

06:07.953 --> 06:10.266
But after comparing
the list of Blair's patients

06:10.300 --> 06:12.164
to the list of potentially
compromised

06:12.199 --> 06:14.374
police investigations
that Nell provided,

06:14.408 --> 06:17.169
the maybe column's
starting to fill up.

06:17.204 --> 06:19.379
- God, you weren't kidding
when you said out of the way.

06:19.413 --> 06:21.691
I think this is where they
store all the old asbestos.

06:21.726 --> 06:23.141
- What?
- It's fine.

06:23.175 --> 06:24.625
Just breathe shallow.

06:24.660 --> 06:26.696
We needed a place where
no one would just wander by.

06:26.731 --> 06:29.527
- And you trusted Smitty
to keep all this a secret?

06:29.561 --> 06:32.461
- We had a conversation about
the consequences of loose lips.

06:32.495 --> 06:34.635
- She threatened to hurt me
in graphic detail.

06:34.670 --> 06:37.051
Used the term "gut dump."

06:37.086 --> 06:40.054
Relax. I won't say nothing
about nothing.

06:40.089 --> 06:41.435
- Guys, I know
who Blair's working for,

06:41.470 --> 06:42.781
and you're not
going to believe it.

06:42.816 --> 06:44.300
- Tell me.
- I did a deep dive.

06:44.334 --> 06:46.198
I mean, we're talking
kindergarten-yearbook deep.

06:46.233 --> 06:48.442
But the answers lay
during her time in grad school,

06:48.477 --> 06:51.411
where Blair London moderated
a student-led panel on insanity

06:51.445 --> 06:52.964
as a legal defense.

06:52.998 --> 06:54.483
- We are
extremely lucky to have

06:54.517 --> 06:56.346
an expert on the nexus
between mental health

06:56.381 --> 06:59.626
and criminal law,
Monica Stevens.

06:59.659 --> 07:01.835
- Son of a puta.
- That makes total sense.

07:01.869 --> 07:04.078
Monica represents half
the criminals in the city.

07:04.113 --> 07:05.977
Selling Blair's intel
on police operations

07:06.011 --> 07:07.979
would make Monica a fortune.

07:08.013 --> 07:09.601
What other evidence
do you have?

07:09.636 --> 07:10.947
- This isn't enough?

07:10.982 --> 07:13.225
- To prove criminal conspiracy?
Not a chance.

07:13.260 --> 07:15.365
To a judge, all that means
is they met three years ago.

07:15.400 --> 07:17.506
We need definitive proof
that the relationship continues

07:17.540 --> 07:19.887
and involves criminal activity.
- Normally, I agree.

07:19.922 --> 07:21.924
But add it to our other
investigations into Monica,

07:21.957 --> 07:23.719
and I say we have enough
to at least get

07:23.753 --> 07:25.928
a wiretap order.
- Maybe. Start writing it up.

07:25.962 --> 07:27.516
I'll go to Grey and see if
he'll authorize

07:27.550 --> 07:28.586
a surveillance unit.

07:28.620 --> 07:30.104
You should notify Chen--
let her know

07:30.139 --> 07:31.796
that her undercover operation
is a top priority.

07:31.830 --> 07:33.970
- Right.
Smitty, get in plain clothes.

07:34.005 --> 07:35.696
I'm adding you
to Lucy's support team.

07:35.731 --> 07:37.111
- Score.

07:37.146 --> 07:39.148
[tense music]

07:39.182 --> 07:40.632
[cell phone chimes]

07:40.667 --> 07:46.396
♪

07:46.431 --> 07:47.605
- Hey, can you kids run inside?

07:47.639 --> 07:49.365
And I'll be right up
and we can play dress-up.

07:49.399 --> 07:50.366
- Sure.
- Yay!

07:50.400 --> 07:51.367
- Okay, thank you.

07:51.401 --> 07:52.851
[line trilling]

07:52.886 --> 07:54.301
- Hello?

07:54.335 --> 07:56.683
- Hey, Mom, um,
I just have a second.

07:56.717 --> 07:58.063
- Monica's
the one running Blair,

07:58.098 --> 07:59.409
but we need to get evidence.

07:59.444 --> 08:00.825
That's now
your mission priority.

08:00.859 --> 08:03.448
- Understood. I haven't seen
her around recently,

08:03.483 --> 08:05.312
but I will keep my eyes peeled.

08:05.346 --> 08:07.038
I got to--I got to go.

08:07.072 --> 08:09.868
Sorry. My mom needed help
answering a question.

08:09.903 --> 08:11.767
- No phone calls
when you're on the clock.

08:11.801 --> 08:13.838
You know that.
- Yeah, it won't happen again.

08:13.872 --> 08:14.908
Sorry.

08:14.942 --> 08:18.808
♪

08:18.843 --> 08:20.810
[elevator bell dings]

08:20.845 --> 08:22.363
- Good morning.

08:22.398 --> 08:24.780
Monica Stevens
to see Eric Ramsey.

08:24.814 --> 08:26.195
I don't have an appointment,

08:26.229 --> 08:28.197
but I do have a sensitive
matter to discuss,

08:28.231 --> 08:30.337
and I'm betting
he'll want to see me.

08:32.165 --> 08:34.789
- Hello, Mr. Ramsey.
Sorry to bother you, sir.

08:34.823 --> 08:37.551
- You can wait out here.
I should be safe inside.

08:37.586 --> 08:39.657
- I'd prefer to at least take
you to his office.

08:39.691 --> 08:42.349
- I appreciate that,
but I'll be fine.

08:42.383 --> 08:45.766
After this crisis is behind us,
we should discuss your future.

08:45.801 --> 08:48.182
I've been impressed.
- Thank you, ma'am.

08:48.217 --> 08:50.184
But I think trying
to protect you long-term

08:50.219 --> 08:51.496
might make my head explode.

08:51.531 --> 08:54.154
No offense intended.
- None taken.

08:54.188 --> 08:55.983
I like the honesty.

08:56.018 --> 08:57.985
- Miss Stevens?

08:58.020 --> 08:59.055
This way.

08:59.090 --> 09:02.576
- [sighs]

09:02.611 --> 09:05.268
Good morning.
Small talk or no?

09:05.303 --> 09:07.063
- No.
- Good.

09:07.098 --> 09:09.065
I know you tried
to have me killed,

09:09.100 --> 09:11.896
though I'm still in the dark as
to what I did to provoke that.

09:11.930 --> 09:13.483
- It's not so much what you did

09:13.518 --> 09:16.003
versus what you could do
down the road.

09:16.038 --> 09:17.798
- You think
I've learned something

09:17.833 --> 09:21.181
about your operation that could
compromise you, but I haven't.

09:21.215 --> 09:23.977
I'd never even heard your name
before yesterday.

09:24.011 --> 09:25.357
- It doesn't matter.

09:25.392 --> 09:27.187
Given the rapid growth
of your information network,

09:27.221 --> 09:28.844
it's only a matter of time
before you do,

09:28.878 --> 09:30.500
and that gives you
leverage over me,

09:30.535 --> 09:31.985
not to mention
something to trade

09:32.019 --> 09:33.503
when you eventually
get arrested.

09:33.538 --> 09:35.609
- Listen, if you've done
your homework about me,

09:35.644 --> 09:37.438
you know that I am ruthless
but practical.

09:37.473 --> 09:39.095
And I'm here to tell you
that there is a deal

09:39.130 --> 09:44.031
to be made after you pay me
a significant apology fee,

09:44.066 --> 09:48.035
of course.
- [chuckles]

09:48.070 --> 09:51.660
Do you know why I'm going
to say no, Miss Stevens?

09:51.694 --> 09:54.835
- No, but I'm excited
for you to tell me.

09:54.870 --> 09:58.287
- Because you--you have
a resources problem.

09:58.321 --> 09:59.702
You provide counsel
and information

09:59.737 --> 10:01.635
to a who's-who of criminals
in this state,

10:01.670 --> 10:03.085
but you don't have a crew.

10:03.119 --> 10:06.226
No one's got your back
unless you pay them,

10:06.260 --> 10:09.505
and I can pay them more
to put a bullet in it.

10:09.539 --> 10:12.439
So I'm going to pass.

10:12.473 --> 10:14.993
- God, that's so foolish.

10:15.028 --> 10:16.823
Do you know why?

10:16.857 --> 10:19.239
You have
an imagination problem.

10:19.273 --> 10:22.311
You're trying to put me in the
same box as your competitors,

10:22.345 --> 10:24.589
be it cartel boss or drug lord.

10:24.624 --> 10:28.731
But I don't fit in that box.

10:28.766 --> 10:31.009
And you don't have
the imagination

10:31.044 --> 10:34.185
to predict the things
that I can do

10:34.219 --> 10:38.776
or conceive of the forces
I can mobilize to end you...

10:38.810 --> 10:42.883
forces that are in play
at this very moment.

10:42.918 --> 10:45.886
[tense music]

10:45.921 --> 10:50.546
♪

10:50.580 --> 10:52.548
[door buzzes]

10:52.582 --> 10:55.551
[indistinct shouting]

10:55.585 --> 10:57.726
[door closes]
- Jason, my man.

10:57.760 --> 10:59.900
- I'm not in the mood
for your B.S. today, Oscar.

10:59.935 --> 11:03.628
- Today my B.S. isn't B.S. but,
in fact, an opportunity for you

11:03.663 --> 11:05.009
to change your life.
- [scoffs]

11:05.043 --> 11:06.907
- Now, I know you're aware
of the recent nuptials

11:06.942 --> 11:09.323
between your former wife
and, well, the man

11:09.358 --> 11:11.049
who put you in prison,
one John Nolan,

11:11.084 --> 11:13.120
and I know that must
be really hard on you.

11:13.155 --> 11:14.604
- Ah, careful.

11:14.639 --> 11:17.573
- How would you like to pay
them a visit, unsupervised,

11:17.607 --> 11:20.334
perhaps in the dead of night
with a cattle prod

11:20.369 --> 11:23.855
and some zip ties?
- [chuckles]

11:23.890 --> 11:26.720
You're messing with me.
Got it.

11:26.755 --> 11:29.861
- I most certainly am not.

11:29.896 --> 11:31.414
I can get you out of here.

11:31.449 --> 11:34.072
I've secured
a VIP exit package,

11:34.107 --> 11:36.281
and I'm willing
to take you with me.

11:36.316 --> 11:38.732
- [chuckles]
Why?

11:40.354 --> 11:44.289
[ominous music]

11:44.324 --> 11:46.084
- In order to secure
this package,

11:46.119 --> 11:49.536
I have to hurt someone in here
to get information.

11:49.570 --> 11:51.918
I need help doing it.

11:51.952 --> 11:54.161
So what do you say?

11:54.196 --> 11:56.646
Spend the rest of your days
locked up here

11:56.681 --> 11:58.683
or give me the next 12 hours
of your life

11:58.718 --> 12:00.789
and be free to get
your wife back?

12:00.823 --> 12:02.963
♪

12:02.998 --> 12:05.034
- My aunt Ximena just adopted.

12:05.069 --> 12:06.035
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

12:06.070 --> 12:07.381
- Boy or girl?
- Boy--Samuel.

12:07.416 --> 12:08.486
He's so cute.

12:08.520 --> 12:10.108
I can connect you two
if you want.

12:10.143 --> 12:11.661
I know it's
an exhaustive process.

12:11.696 --> 12:13.284
- Yeah, that would be great.
Thank you for that.

12:13.318 --> 12:14.941
- Has Bailey said yes yet?

12:14.975 --> 12:17.150
- No, not yet.
But she will.

12:17.184 --> 12:18.979
I'm pretty sure.

12:19.014 --> 12:20.809
- [sighs]
- What's wrong?

12:20.843 --> 12:23.018
- Judge wouldn't sign off
on the Monica warrant,

12:23.052 --> 12:25.399
said we need more to overcome
the attorney-client factor.

12:25.434 --> 12:26.780
So I need you to push Blair.

12:26.815 --> 12:28.782
She came to you first.
She might talk to you now.

12:28.817 --> 12:30.335
Tell her we know about Monica

12:30.370 --> 12:32.441
and that if she doesn't come in
and start talking immediately,

12:32.475 --> 12:34.098
she's going into gen-pop
at the Twin Towers

12:34.132 --> 12:35.789
and she'll be
dead by nightfall.

12:35.824 --> 12:38.171
- So scare the crap out of her.
Got it.

12:38.205 --> 12:39.620
[cell phone beeps]

12:39.655 --> 12:41.761
[line trilling]

12:43.728 --> 12:45.799
[cell phone ringing]

12:45.834 --> 12:47.352
- I've got nothing
to say to you.

12:47.387 --> 12:49.216
- Good, 'cause I just
need you to listen.

12:49.251 --> 12:50.942
We know you're
in bed with Monica.

12:53.427 --> 12:56.189
- I wanted to help people.

12:56.223 --> 12:58.398
I wanted to do something
meaningful with my life,

12:58.432 --> 13:00.710
and she twisted everything.

13:00.745 --> 13:04.473
Now two of my patients
are dead, and it's my fault.

13:04.507 --> 13:07.821
I should have stood up to her,
but I was too afraid.

13:07.856 --> 13:09.892
- You can still
make this right.

13:09.927 --> 13:11.583
Just testify against her.

13:11.618 --> 13:14.103
- It's too dangerous.
She has spies everywhere.

13:14.138 --> 13:15.691
- No, the FBI is involved now.

13:15.725 --> 13:18.245
That means you'll be
in federal protective custody.

13:18.280 --> 13:20.109
So it doesn't matter
how deep Monica

13:20.144 --> 13:22.042
has her claws
into the department,

13:22.077 --> 13:24.010
but that means
I need a yes right now.

13:24.044 --> 13:26.046
Otherwise,
you're going to be pulled over

13:26.081 --> 13:29.118
and arrested with great fanfare
over an open radio channel.

13:29.153 --> 13:31.431
- Okay.
What do I do?

13:33.157 --> 13:36.401
[cell phone ringing]

13:36.436 --> 13:37.989
- Yeah?
- It's Lopez.

13:38.024 --> 13:39.163
Blair's taking the deal.

13:39.197 --> 13:40.750
She's heading down
to FBI headquarters now.

13:40.785 --> 13:42.062
Stay with Blair.

13:42.097 --> 13:44.789
Harper and I will meet you
down there.

13:44.824 --> 13:47.309
- [screams]

13:47.343 --> 13:51.831
- Dr. London,
unlock your car and let me in.

13:51.865 --> 13:55.455
Do it now, or I'll shoot you
in the face.

13:55.489 --> 13:57.595
[gearshift clacks]

13:57.629 --> 14:01.910
[dramatic music]

14:01.944 --> 14:05.396
If you try anything, I'll put
a bullet through your spine.

14:05.430 --> 14:07.536
Are we clear?
- Yes.

14:07.570 --> 14:09.952
♪

14:09.987 --> 14:11.851
- Take a left.

14:11.885 --> 14:14.370
We're going to see Monica.
[engine turning over]

14:14.405 --> 14:18.892
♪

14:21.826 --> 14:23.414
- [yelling]

14:25.968 --> 14:27.694
Oh, you guys are dead.

14:27.728 --> 14:30.007
You can't just jump me and my
crew and get away with it.

14:30.041 --> 14:31.663
- Sure, I can.
You know why?

14:31.698 --> 14:32.906
Because we're not
going to be here

14:32.941 --> 14:35.426
long enough for retribution
to come calling.

14:35.460 --> 14:38.394
- [yelling]

14:43.123 --> 14:45.160
- [groans]

14:48.957 --> 14:50.682
- Listen,
I need you to overcome

14:50.717 --> 14:53.133
your recalcitrant nature

14:53.168 --> 14:55.895
and answer my questions
about your boss,

14:55.929 --> 14:57.206
Eric Ramsey.

14:57.241 --> 15:00.382
- [scoffs] Never happen.
I'm not a rat.

15:00.416 --> 15:03.385
- See, that's really
a dirty, ugly term, you know.

15:03.419 --> 15:05.007
As a guy who has ratted out

15:05.042 --> 15:07.872
a baker's dozen of his
best friends over the years,

15:07.907 --> 15:09.805
I can say that it hurts
a lot less

15:09.839 --> 15:13.395
than my pal Jason here breaking
every bone in your body

15:13.429 --> 15:17.157
one at a time,
starting with the elbow.

15:17.192 --> 15:20.402
[bone crunches]
- [yells]

15:20.436 --> 15:22.645
- Tell me about Ramsey.

15:24.199 --> 15:26.615
[cell phone ringing]

15:29.790 --> 15:31.585
- You better have good news.

15:31.620 --> 15:35.693
- Oh, boy, do I. Your nemesis
has a rich benefactor.

15:35.727 --> 15:37.764
He's Swiss,
billionaire-adjacent,

15:37.798 --> 15:40.525
does business in
South America and East Asia--

15:40.560 --> 15:42.079
Jakob Olmstead.

15:42.113 --> 15:43.701
- How does that help me?

15:43.735 --> 15:46.393
- Well, Mr. Olmstead
is an apex predator

15:46.428 --> 15:48.948
who's not going to take
too kindly to finding out

15:48.982 --> 15:53.055
that Eric Ramsay has been
banging his wife on the sly.

15:53.090 --> 15:55.161
- Thank you.

15:55.195 --> 15:57.370
The wheels have been greased
at your location,

15:57.404 --> 15:59.959
and resources are in place
for your departure.

15:59.993 --> 16:02.685
Good luck.
- Back at ya.

16:02.720 --> 16:05.240
- Good news?

16:05.274 --> 16:08.243
- Feels like it.
[elevator bell dings]

16:08.277 --> 16:11.246
[tense music]

16:11.280 --> 16:13.317
[distant tires screeching]

16:16.492 --> 16:18.356
- Stop!

16:18.391 --> 16:20.427
No, no, no.

16:20.462 --> 16:22.188
- It's okay.
It's okay.

16:22.222 --> 16:25.398
If Gundo wanted to kill me,
we'd be dead already.

16:25.432 --> 16:27.020
Easy.

16:30.161 --> 16:31.783
What can I do for you?

16:31.818 --> 16:36.133
- Amazing. I got offered half
a million dollars to kill you.

16:36.167 --> 16:40.654
But I'm here to give you
the opportunity to top that--

16:40.689 --> 16:44.762
2 million,
plus 10% of your business.

16:44.796 --> 16:46.419
- That's a ballsy ask.

16:46.453 --> 16:47.799
- Is it?

16:47.834 --> 16:50.457
Because it seems to
me you got no choice.

16:50.492 --> 16:53.667
♪

16:53.702 --> 16:56.153
- It'll take me until tonight
to get the cash together.

16:56.187 --> 16:58.327
- [speaking in Spanish]

16:58.362 --> 17:00.571
5:00 at the laundromat.

17:02.055 --> 17:03.125
We're good, vatos.

17:03.160 --> 17:06.059
Ya vamos!

17:06.094 --> 17:08.303
Don't you be late.

17:08.337 --> 17:15.378
♪

17:17.415 --> 17:18.727
[engine turning over]

17:18.761 --> 17:20.729
- Okay.
Now I'm calling the police.

17:20.762 --> 17:22.523
- No, you're not.

17:22.558 --> 17:25.009
I told you, they don't have
my best interests at heart.

17:25.044 --> 17:27.184
- They're not actively
conspiring to kill you.

17:27.218 --> 17:28.840
- This is not a negotiation.

17:28.875 --> 17:31.188
Okay, look, I understand
that operating this way

17:31.222 --> 17:32.706
is difficult for you.

17:32.741 --> 17:35.813
So I'll add a hearty hazard
bonus to your fee.

17:35.847 --> 17:37.401
Say 100K?

17:39.541 --> 17:41.060
- Fine, no cops.

17:41.094 --> 17:42.647
But I'm pulling help back in.

17:42.682 --> 17:44.511
I'll get them to meet us
at the office.

17:44.546 --> 17:46.789
- No, we're not going
to the office just yet.

17:46.824 --> 17:48.308
- Where are we going?

17:48.343 --> 17:53.106
♪

17:53.141 --> 17:56.144
[slurping]

17:58.456 --> 17:59.940
[keypad clicking]

17:59.975 --> 18:01.252
[cell phone chimes]

18:01.287 --> 18:04.048
♪

18:04.083 --> 18:07.465
Sorry.
[clears throat]

18:07.500 --> 18:14.472
♪

18:17.268 --> 18:18.304
- Hey.

18:18.338 --> 18:20.375
It is so nice outside.

18:20.409 --> 18:21.893
Why don't we go outside
and play?

18:21.928 --> 18:24.103
- Yeah.
- Yeah? Okay, let's go.

18:24.137 --> 18:31.110
♪

18:38.600 --> 18:39.704
- This way.

18:39.739 --> 18:40.843
- N-no.

18:40.878 --> 18:42.776
Uh, let's--let's go
to the back.

18:42.811 --> 18:45.365
- All right.
- Yeah, let's go. Sorry, sorry.

18:45.400 --> 18:49.473
♪

18:53.062 --> 18:55.203
- Hey. Angela tell you we ran
into each other at the station?

18:55.237 --> 18:57.619
- She did.
That's why I'm calling.

18:57.653 --> 18:59.103
I'm worried
you don't understand

18:59.138 --> 19:00.587
who you're working for.

19:00.622 --> 19:02.658
- I don't talk
about my protectees to anyone,

19:02.693 --> 19:04.833
especially former clients
in law enforcement.

19:04.867 --> 19:07.215
- I respect that, but you
need to protect yourself.

19:07.249 --> 19:09.631
Monica is involved in an active
criminal conspiracy--

19:09.665 --> 19:11.046
one dead cop, one missing,

19:11.080 --> 19:13.186
and a police psychiatrist
was just abducted.

19:13.221 --> 19:15.533
- You think Monica's kidnapping
people in those heels?

19:15.568 --> 19:17.501
- I know how she
represents herself.

19:17.535 --> 19:19.641
But you've been
with her for a few days now.

19:19.675 --> 19:22.678
I think you're starting to see
things that feel wrong,

19:22.713 --> 19:24.680
things that make
you uncomfortable.

19:24.715 --> 19:27.166
♪

19:27.200 --> 19:29.168
- She'll be back soon.
I have to go.

19:29.202 --> 19:31.756
- Charlie, think about it,
not just for us, for you.

19:31.791 --> 19:33.793
Things are coming to a head,
and when they do,

19:33.827 --> 19:36.796
you want to make sure you're
standing on the right side.

19:36.830 --> 19:38.798
♪

19:38.832 --> 19:41.490
- I'm here to make you an offer
you can't refuse.

19:41.525 --> 19:42.836
- Keep talking.

19:42.871 --> 19:44.838
- I know who's trying
to have me killed,

19:44.873 --> 19:47.462
and I want to pay you
an obscene amount of money

19:47.496 --> 19:49.015
to help me strike back.

19:49.049 --> 19:52.087
- I already have
an obscene amount of money.

19:52.121 --> 19:53.744
- You have Hollywood money.

19:53.778 --> 19:55.332
I'll make you Wall Street rich,

19:55.366 --> 19:58.438
starting with a guarantee of 5%
of my business,

19:58.473 --> 20:00.647
followed by an introduction
to a Swiss benefactor

20:00.682 --> 20:02.960
that'll take
your money-laundering business

20:02.994 --> 20:04.996
international.

20:05.031 --> 20:08.586
All you have to do is send
a hit team to a laundromat.

20:27.467 --> 20:29.504
[door closes]

20:32.161 --> 20:34.647
I'm glad we could come
to an agreement.

20:34.681 --> 20:35.958
- Likewise.

20:35.993 --> 20:38.513
I'll make the call.
Shouldn't take long.

20:47.315 --> 20:50.283
[suspenseful music]

20:50.318 --> 20:54.391
♪

20:54.425 --> 20:57.325
I need some cleaning done,
Sixth Street Laundromat--

20:57.359 --> 20:59.258
two teams, no mercy.

20:59.292 --> 21:01.052
- Oh.
[chuckles]

21:01.087 --> 21:02.916
- What are you doing?
- I'm sorry.

21:02.951 --> 21:07.127
I was just looking for, um,
Esther's favorite headband.

21:07.162 --> 21:08.853
- Go pack the kids' bags.

21:08.888 --> 21:11.373
L.A.'s too hot right now.
We're going somewhere cooler.

21:11.408 --> 21:13.133
- Should I go home
and pack my bag as well?

21:13.168 --> 21:14.514
- No need, family only.

21:14.549 --> 21:16.102
Vera will call you
when we're back.

21:16.136 --> 21:17.241
- Oh, okay.

21:17.276 --> 21:20.244
[tense music]

21:20.279 --> 21:23.385
♪

21:23.420 --> 21:25.214
[line trilling]

21:25.249 --> 21:27.251
Hey, Mom, I got news.

21:27.286 --> 21:28.701
There's a storm coming,

21:28.735 --> 21:31.497
but I need you to figure out
who it's gonna hit.

21:31.531 --> 21:38.504
♪

21:38.538 --> 21:40.575
- Now to the office?
- No.

21:40.609 --> 21:43.163
Airport, private terminal.

21:43.198 --> 21:45.718
I have a flight to catch.

21:45.752 --> 21:47.064
[engine turning over]

21:47.098 --> 21:48.548
- This laundromat
serves as the home base

21:48.583 --> 21:50.067
for Gundo's drug business.

21:50.101 --> 21:51.931
- Wait. Wasn't Gundo helping
Monica just yesterday?

21:51.965 --> 21:53.346
What happened?

21:53.381 --> 21:54.968
- She's not exactly
known for her loyalty.

21:55.003 --> 21:57.902
- We can ask Gundo all about
it, assuming we keep him alive.

21:57.937 --> 22:00.249
- From a strategic standpoint,
this place is a death trap.

22:00.284 --> 22:02.804
There's only two exits--one
in the front and one in back.

22:02.838 --> 22:04.426
- Hey.
Heard you guys needed backup.

22:04.461 --> 22:05.910
The Batistas just left town.

22:05.945 --> 22:07.774
- Yeah, well, if I put a hit
out on Gundo, I'd bail, too.

22:07.809 --> 22:09.466
- Well, the FBI
are tracking them.

22:09.500 --> 22:11.606
So, once we make a solid case,
they'll make the arrest.

22:11.640 --> 22:13.573
- It's good to have you.

22:13.608 --> 22:14.850
- Thanks.

22:14.885 --> 22:17.197
So what's the plan?

22:17.232 --> 22:20.200
[suspenseful music]

22:20.235 --> 22:27.000
♪

22:32.799 --> 22:34.698
- I really should be going
with you.

22:34.732 --> 22:36.458
- Thanks, but I'm covered.

22:36.493 --> 22:42.050
♪

22:42.084 --> 22:43.983
- There you are.
- Please don't kill me.

22:44.017 --> 22:45.709
I didn't tell them anything.
[engine turning over]

22:45.743 --> 22:48.436
- You got the next 20 hours
to convince me that's true.

22:48.470 --> 22:53.406
♪

22:53.441 --> 22:56.582
[cell phone ringing]

22:56.616 --> 22:58.722
- Charlie.

22:58.756 --> 23:00.344
Charlie?

23:00.379 --> 23:02.588
- Monica's leaving the country.

23:02.622 --> 23:04.279
I just dropped her
at a private plane,

23:04.313 --> 23:05.625
and she's not going alone.

23:05.660 --> 23:07.006
There was hired muscle

23:07.040 --> 23:09.008
and a woman that didn't look
too happy to be going.

23:09.042 --> 23:10.630
- What did she look like?

23:10.665 --> 23:12.977
- Late 20s, Caucasian, petite,

23:13.012 --> 23:15.048
shoulder-length
brown hair, pretty.

23:15.083 --> 23:16.256
- Blair.

23:16.291 --> 23:17.810
Any chance you get
the tail number?

23:17.844 --> 23:20.053
- Do you have a pen?

23:20.088 --> 23:21.400
- Make yourself comfortable.

23:21.434 --> 23:23.436
Monica is on her way
to Argentina.

23:23.471 --> 23:25.438
- Oh, that is great,
because I am running on fumes.

23:25.473 --> 23:26.715
I could use the sleep.

23:26.750 --> 23:28.545
Ooh, I love the hair.
- You too.

23:28.579 --> 23:29.787
- What's this?

23:29.822 --> 23:31.548
- Desert-wear,
so you're dressed properly.

23:31.582 --> 23:33.722
It's gonna be dusty.
- Is it cute?

23:33.757 --> 23:35.034
- Oh, please.
Girl, I got you.

23:35.068 --> 23:36.276
- Very fashionable.

23:36.311 --> 23:37.968
All right, so who are we
working with in-country?

23:38.002 --> 23:40.039
- Local contractors,
CIA-adjacent,

23:40.073 --> 23:41.385
strictly tour guides.

23:41.420 --> 23:42.938
- Why not local law?

23:42.973 --> 23:45.044
- Because we have no proof
that Blair was kidnapped.

23:45.078 --> 23:47.529
Charlie saw her get on
the plane on her own volition.

23:47.564 --> 23:49.462
- So local law enforcement
will not intervene?

23:49.497 --> 23:50.705
- That's right.

23:50.739 --> 23:52.292
Officially, I'm there
to "collect intelligence

23:52.327 --> 23:54.156
from a confidential
local resource."

23:54.191 --> 23:55.986
- Okay, why am I there?
- You're not.

23:56.020 --> 23:58.367
- And if we do
find out that Blair is,

23:58.402 --> 24:00.680
in fact, kidnapped and being
held against her will,

24:00.715 --> 24:02.717
what do we do then?
- Nothing.

24:02.751 --> 24:04.270
- You are here
to observe and report.

24:04.304 --> 24:06.375
We'll bring any evidence
to our liaison at State,

24:06.410 --> 24:08.067
who will then pass it along
to local authorities.

24:08.101 --> 24:09.620
- By which time two weeks
will have passed.

24:09.655 --> 24:11.519
By then, she'll be
either dead or MIA.

24:11.553 --> 24:13.693
- But we would consider
a hostage rescue,

24:13.728 --> 24:15.557
they might consider
a kidnapping.

24:15.592 --> 24:17.594
- They can fight us
with automatic weapons, John.

24:17.628 --> 24:19.492
We can't legally possess
a slingshot,

24:19.527 --> 24:21.321
so we observe and report.

24:21.356 --> 24:24.359
If you don't like it, I suggest
you get off this plane now.

24:26.016 --> 24:29.537
- [sighs] At least we'll look
good doing nothing.

24:34.956 --> 24:36.060
- ♪ One-two

24:36.095 --> 24:40.789
♪

24:40.824 --> 24:43.205
♪ Wanna step into the ring?

24:43.240 --> 24:44.828
♪ I'll hit you with the

24:44.862 --> 24:46.588
♪ I'll hit you
with the one-two ♪

24:46.623 --> 24:48.072
- Reporting for duty.

24:48.107 --> 24:50.212
Grey said you'd be taking over
as my T.O.

24:50.247 --> 24:52.905
since Nolan is
otherwise engaged.

24:52.939 --> 24:54.078
- Define "furtherance."

24:54.113 --> 24:56.046
- Well, in this case,
it involves

24:56.080 --> 24:58.117
approaching the victim
with a deadly weapon

24:58.151 --> 24:59.532
in attempt to engage.

24:59.567 --> 25:01.569
Until they do, the DA
won't be able to charge

25:01.603 --> 25:03.432
attempted murder.
- Correct.

25:03.467 --> 25:05.193
If we arrest
Christian's guys too early,

25:05.227 --> 25:06.988
we get them on a misdemeanor
gun possession,

25:07.022 --> 25:08.265
they're out in an hour.

25:08.299 --> 25:09.991
They hit Gundo
before we even know about it.

25:10.025 --> 25:11.613
This is our only chance.
You ready?

25:11.648 --> 25:13.097
- Yes, sir.

25:13.132 --> 25:15.134
- Stay glued to Aaron's hip
for the duration of the op.

25:15.168 --> 25:16.549
All right,
everybody, listen up.

25:16.584 --> 25:18.378
Detective Lopez is going
to be our red zone point

25:18.413 --> 25:19.621
dressed as an unhoused person.

25:19.656 --> 25:21.105
Get a good look.

25:21.140 --> 25:22.969
- Please don't shoot
the crazy lady

25:23.004 --> 25:25.558
pushing the stroller
full of trash--thank you.

25:25.593 --> 25:28.009
- Listen, we're expecting
an A-side frontal attack

25:28.043 --> 25:30.390
from an unknown number
of suspects.

25:30.425 --> 25:32.669
Gundo's inside already.

25:32.703 --> 25:35.050
All right, keep in mind
school just got out.

25:35.085 --> 25:36.673
So watch your muzzle,
watch your partner,

25:36.707 --> 25:37.846
watch your backstop.

25:37.881 --> 25:39.641
Front-sight focus,
no mistakes.

25:39.676 --> 25:41.574
Officer Chen and I will cover
the rear,

25:41.609 --> 25:44.646
and we'll call for backup
in case of a C-side attack.

25:54.863 --> 25:57.072
So I took your advice.

25:57.107 --> 25:59.834
I went to therapy.
- And?

25:59.868 --> 26:01.421
- And my therapist

26:01.456 --> 26:03.838
turned out to be
a blackmailing psychopath.

26:03.872 --> 26:07.427
- [scoffs] You know
that's not normal, right?

26:07.462 --> 26:10.845
One bad experience shouldn't
tar the whole profession.

26:10.879 --> 26:13.088
- Want to know the irony?

26:13.123 --> 26:15.263
- Yeah.

26:15.297 --> 26:17.610
- She was a good therapist.

26:17.645 --> 26:18.853
Opened the door on some stuff

26:18.887 --> 26:20.820
that I didn't even know
was in there.

26:20.855 --> 26:24.030
And now all those confessions
are living up in the cloud,

26:24.065 --> 26:27.516
waiting for some FBI IT guy
to come unencrypt them

26:27.551 --> 26:30.899
so they can be analyzed
for evidentiary value.

26:30.934 --> 26:32.660
- I'm sorry.

26:34.765 --> 26:39.011
Did you tell her anything
revealing about me?

26:40.288 --> 26:41.841
- Um...

26:41.876 --> 26:46.052
I believe the term I used
was "freak in the sheets."

26:46.087 --> 26:48.503
- You're the worst.
[both chuckle]

26:48.537 --> 26:49.815
- Point has a possible.

26:49.849 --> 26:53.577
Black four-door landing,
occupied four times.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.027
Christian's guys are on foot.

26:55.061 --> 26:58.202
They're wearing black hoodies,
red sneakers, black masks.

26:58.237 --> 27:00.653
I see bulges under their
shirts, possible weapons.

27:00.688 --> 27:02.310
Repeat, possible weapons only.

27:02.344 --> 27:04.623
- Arrest teams,
move closer, but stay hidden.

27:04.657 --> 27:05.969
Do not engage
till guns come out.

27:06.003 --> 27:09.593
- They're coming now,
15 yards away.

27:09.628 --> 27:11.975
12 yards out,
no weapons visible.

27:13.701 --> 27:16.324
Wait. One of them stopped.
They're making a phone call.

27:16.358 --> 27:19.327
[dramatic music]

27:19.361 --> 27:26.403
♪

27:33.686 --> 27:35.412
- They just blocked
the back door.

27:36.931 --> 27:39.347
- Front 3 are on the move
again, about 10 yards out.

27:39.381 --> 27:42.281
♪

27:42.315 --> 27:43.523
- All right, get that guy.

27:43.558 --> 27:45.284
I got the back door.
- Yeah.

27:45.318 --> 27:50.047
♪

27:50.082 --> 27:52.256
[engine turning over,
tires squealing]

27:52.291 --> 27:55.501
♪

27:55.535 --> 27:57.227
- Ten seconds out,
no weapons visible.

27:57.261 --> 28:00.161
Wait, we got kids
in the crossfire. Gun!

28:02.232 --> 28:04.510
[people shouting]

28:06.857 --> 28:10.378
[siren wailing]
[breathing heavily]

28:10.412 --> 28:12.449
- Go help Lopez!

28:12.483 --> 28:14.140
- Hey, you okay?

28:14.175 --> 28:18.904
- Code-4. Vest saved me,
but I'm gonna hurt tomorrow.

28:18.938 --> 28:21.665
[gunshots]

28:23.736 --> 28:25.048
We need him alive!

28:25.082 --> 28:31.848
♪

28:31.882 --> 28:34.713
- Aah!

28:34.747 --> 28:41.754
♪

28:45.793 --> 28:47.726
[car door closes,
engine turning over]

28:47.760 --> 28:50.625
[tires squealing]

28:50.659 --> 28:57.563
♪

28:57.597 --> 28:58.875
- Wes, take this guy!

28:58.909 --> 29:00.669
Tim's in the back
of that truck.

29:00.704 --> 29:03.880
♪

29:03.914 --> 29:05.882
[tires squealing]

29:05.916 --> 29:12.958
♪

29:17.963 --> 29:19.240
- Ugh!

29:19.274 --> 29:25.971
♪

29:43.747 --> 29:46.163
[tires squealing]

29:46.198 --> 29:53.239
♪

29:56.553 --> 29:58.693
Lopez, take the wheel.

29:58.727 --> 30:00.177
[car beeps]

30:00.212 --> 30:07.253
♪

30:12.224 --> 30:15.158
[The Hives's "Tick Tick Boom"]

30:15.192 --> 30:20.266
♪

30:20.301 --> 30:24.132
- ♪ Yeah,
I was right all along ♪

30:24.167 --> 30:27.377
♪

30:27.411 --> 30:31.450
♪ Yeah,
you come tagging along ♪

30:31.484 --> 30:33.762
♪

30:33.797 --> 30:38.664
♪ Exhibit A,
I was wrong all along ♪

30:40.252 --> 30:42.633
♪ 'Cause I have
done it before ♪

30:42.668 --> 30:45.671
♪ And I can do it some more,
I got my eye on the score ♪

30:45.705 --> 30:47.638
♪ I'm gonna cut
through the floor ♪

30:47.673 --> 30:50.262
♪ It's too late,
it's too soon, or is it? ♪

30:50.296 --> 30:54.749
♪ Tick, tick, tick,
tick, tick, tick, boom ♪

31:25.745 --> 31:29.163
- I need you to hear me.
This mission is not authorized.

31:29.197 --> 31:31.303
- Relax.
This is not an operation.

31:31.337 --> 31:32.891
It's a fact-finding visit.

31:32.925 --> 31:34.513
There's no reason
why the State Department

31:34.547 --> 31:35.963
should be concerned.

31:35.997 --> 31:38.103
- That's what they said
about the iceberg in "Titanic."

31:38.137 --> 31:40.381
I want it on record, I told
you guys to get on the plane

31:40.415 --> 31:43.280
and go home.
- Noted.

31:43.315 --> 31:45.110
Special Agent Matt Garza.
- Hey.

31:45.144 --> 31:47.664
- This is Laura and Brendon.
They work with me at FBI.

31:47.698 --> 31:49.873
Nyla Harper, John Nolan, LAPD.

31:49.908 --> 31:52.358
- Shawn Miller. That's Lee.
Nice to meet you all.

31:52.393 --> 31:54.947
Your target plane landed
approximately 20 minutes ago--

31:54.982 --> 31:56.293
4 individuals,

31:56.328 --> 31:58.330
including Monica Stevens
and Blair London.

31:58.364 --> 32:00.159
I don't have IDs
on the other two.

32:00.194 --> 32:01.747
- Uh, may I?
- Sure.

32:01.781 --> 32:03.576
- Just run it
through our system,

32:03.611 --> 32:05.924
see if I can't put some names
to some faces.

32:05.958 --> 32:07.891
All right, all right, got it.
Thanks.

32:07.926 --> 32:09.755
- Any intel
on who Monica's meeting?

32:09.789 --> 32:12.654
- Not officially, but rumor is
it's Jakob Olmstead.

32:12.689 --> 32:14.035
- Never heard of him.

32:14.070 --> 32:15.830
- He's a Swiss money guy
with ties

32:15.864 --> 32:18.143
to all forms of trafficking--
guns, girls, drugs.

32:18.177 --> 32:21.077
The FBI's been trying to hang
a case on him for a decade.

32:21.111 --> 32:24.597
This just got interesting.
- Sure did.

32:24.632 --> 32:27.152
- Uh, I thought we were meant
to be unarmed.

32:27.186 --> 32:29.740
- You are, so those weapons
are staying in their cases.

32:29.775 --> 32:31.811
All right, let's move out.

32:36.989 --> 32:39.992
[engines turning over]

32:46.412 --> 32:48.173
- I don't like it.
- Tough.

32:48.207 --> 32:50.520
If we show up to the meeting
armed for a war,

32:50.554 --> 32:52.591
we're going to get ourselves
into one.

32:52.625 --> 32:55.318
The guns stay in the car.
- Yes, ma'am.

33:00.530 --> 33:02.566
- [sniffles]

33:02.601 --> 33:06.225
- Pull yourself together.
It's not the end of the world.

33:06.260 --> 33:08.296
The alternative
is a lot more final.

33:08.331 --> 33:10.471
- I never should have agreed
to helping you.

33:10.505 --> 33:13.439
- [laughing]
Please.

33:13.474 --> 33:16.063
Your fate was sealed when you
called me three years ago

33:16.097 --> 33:17.547
to clean up your mess.

33:17.581 --> 33:20.412
- I was drunk and scared.

33:20.446 --> 33:23.898
- And had just run
someone over.

33:23.932 --> 33:25.900
If I hadn't made
that body go away,

33:25.934 --> 33:29.248
you'd be getting your
psych degree from a prison.

33:29.283 --> 33:32.665
So show a little gratitude.

33:32.700 --> 33:34.633
And fix your face.

33:34.667 --> 33:37.705
You need to look pretty
for Mr. Olmstead.

33:39.362 --> 33:43.228
[Beethoven's
"Coriolan Overture"]

33:43.262 --> 33:45.471
[bird screeches]

33:45.506 --> 33:48.267
♪

33:48.302 --> 33:51.408
- That's my good girl.

33:51.443 --> 33:58.484
♪

34:08.873 --> 34:10.945
Thanks.

34:10.978 --> 34:14.085
- Keep her with you for now.

34:14.121 --> 34:16.813
- Yeah, it's a party,
and Charlie was right.

34:16.847 --> 34:20.610
Blair does not look happy
to be in attendance.

34:20.643 --> 34:22.197
- Okay, yeah.

34:22.232 --> 34:23.958
ID'd our mystery muscle.

34:23.992 --> 34:26.304
Lots of aliases over the years,
but their birth names are

34:26.340 --> 34:27.789
Paige Baker, Pascal Moreau.

34:27.824 --> 34:29.170
She's Irish, he's French.

34:29.205 --> 34:31.552
No current wants,
but a history of mayhem

34:31.585 --> 34:33.105
across three continents.
- Okay.

34:33.139 --> 34:35.521
- Mr. Olmstead, thank you
for agreeing to see me.

34:35.556 --> 34:37.764
- Hard to say no when you claim
to have knowledge

34:37.799 --> 34:39.179
that will save my life.

34:39.215 --> 34:41.043
- I wish I could say
I was being dramatic.

34:41.079 --> 34:42.666
But I have learned
over the years

34:42.701 --> 34:45.393
as a lawyer for dangerous men
that the first appearance

34:45.428 --> 34:48.914
of disrespect is the first step
towards betrayal.

34:48.947 --> 34:51.848
- And who do you think
is disrespecting me?

34:51.882 --> 34:53.918
- Eric Ramsey...

34:53.953 --> 34:55.300
and your wife.

34:57.612 --> 34:58.820
- You have proof of this?

34:58.855 --> 35:01.513
- Yes, hotel video
from three separate trips

35:01.547 --> 35:03.722
your wife took to Los Angeles
over the last year.

35:03.756 --> 35:05.896
And I'm also
in the process of securing

35:05.931 --> 35:09.348
additional footage from a trip
she took to Las Vegas in...

35:09.383 --> 35:10.901
October?

35:10.936 --> 35:12.455
- September.

35:16.183 --> 35:20.221
[sighs] How do you expect to be
rewarded for this information?

35:20.256 --> 35:22.154
- I have a request.

35:25.640 --> 35:30.058
- It looks like Monica is
handing Blair over to Olmstead.

35:30.093 --> 35:33.200
Are we just gonna watch?
- We don't have a choice.

35:33.234 --> 35:34.787
- He's right.

35:34.822 --> 35:36.996
- Then he can stay here.

35:37.031 --> 35:40.621
- Whoa.
I can't let you do that.

35:40.655 --> 35:42.381
- Damn it!
Nolan!

35:42.416 --> 35:44.935
[dramatic rock music]

35:44.970 --> 35:46.903
[engine turning over]

35:46.937 --> 35:50.907
♪

35:50.941 --> 35:54.462
- After you've removed
Mr. Ramsey from the picture,

35:54.497 --> 35:56.533
I would like the opportunity
to show you

35:56.568 --> 35:58.294
why I should take his place.

35:58.328 --> 36:00.882
I am not asking for a handout.

36:00.917 --> 36:03.471
I will prove my value.

36:03.506 --> 36:05.784
- Fair enough.

36:05.818 --> 36:07.613
Who is this?

36:07.648 --> 36:09.822
- A new friend.

36:09.857 --> 36:13.447
- Is she another problem
you're solving?

36:13.481 --> 36:16.243
[dramatic rock music]

36:16.277 --> 36:18.486
- All right,
what's your plan here, John?

36:18.521 --> 36:20.419
- This thing's
bulletproof, right?

36:20.454 --> 36:22.318
- That is not a plan.

36:22.352 --> 36:29.325
♪

36:29.359 --> 36:30.636
[indistinct shouting]

36:30.671 --> 36:33.467
- Move! Move! Move! Move!

36:33.501 --> 36:36.470
[rapid gunfire]

36:36.504 --> 36:39.645
[indistinct shouting]

36:39.680 --> 36:46.721
♪

37:00.701 --> 37:02.254
- Get in the Humvee.

37:02.289 --> 37:09.261
♪

37:13.196 --> 37:14.266
- Nolan!

37:14.301 --> 37:18.857
[gunfire echoing]

37:18.891 --> 37:20.790
Nolan! Get up!

37:24.276 --> 37:25.898
- Nolan!

37:25.933 --> 37:29.247
- [grunting]
[gunfire echoing]

37:29.281 --> 37:30.903
Nolan, move!

37:30.938 --> 37:34.459
[gunfire]

37:34.493 --> 37:37.738
Nolan, we have to go now!
Move!

37:41.086 --> 37:43.122
- [grunting]

37:45.539 --> 37:47.506
- How bad?
- Not bad. It hurts.

37:47.541 --> 37:51.752
Just got the meat.
- I can stop the bleeding.

37:51.786 --> 37:53.271
- Harper, we got trouble.

37:53.305 --> 37:56.515
[tense music]

37:56.550 --> 38:01.624
♪

38:01.658 --> 38:04.178
- Go, go, go!

38:04.212 --> 38:05.386
- Talk to me.

38:05.421 --> 38:07.802
Is everybody okay?
- No. Nolan got shot.

38:07.837 --> 38:09.114
It doesn't seems too bad,

38:09.148 --> 38:10.598
but we need a medevac chopper
just in case.

38:10.633 --> 38:11.910
- I'm on it.

38:11.944 --> 38:14.602
[tense music]

38:14.637 --> 38:19.952
♪

38:19.987 --> 38:21.920
[door buzzes]
- I'm sorry.

38:21.954 --> 38:23.266
- Save it.

38:23.301 --> 38:24.371
- I know that doesn't make up

38:24.405 --> 38:26.165
for what I did to you,
to everyone.

38:26.200 --> 38:27.477
- I said "save it."

38:28.961 --> 38:31.239
You know, a therapist
I once thought I could trust

38:31.274 --> 38:33.759
told me that I need to set
boundaries for myself.

38:33.794 --> 38:36.555
And that's exactly
what I'm doing.

38:36.590 --> 38:38.350
Hey, can you finish
processing her for me?

38:38.385 --> 38:39.765
- Sure.

38:39.800 --> 38:42.389
- ♪ I think I see it
on the horizon ♪

38:42.423 --> 38:44.011
- She talked
the whole way back?

38:44.045 --> 38:45.357
- All 16 hours.

38:45.392 --> 38:47.842
Clearly, she had a lot
to unburden herself of.

38:47.877 --> 38:49.016
- How's Nolan?

38:49.050 --> 38:50.569
- Oh, they patched him up
at the base.

38:50.604 --> 38:52.364
It was a clean
through-and-through.

38:52.399 --> 38:54.573
He insisted on going home
when we landed,

38:54.608 --> 38:58.370
and since Bailey's an EMT,
we figured it was safe enough.

38:58.405 --> 39:00.614
- Any idea what happened
to Monica?

39:00.648 --> 39:02.270
- No, but she is on the run.

39:02.305 --> 39:04.514
Garza put out
an Interpol warrant on her.

39:04.549 --> 39:05.826
So it's only a matter of time

39:05.860 --> 39:09.001
before someone catches up
to her and ships her home.

39:09.036 --> 39:11.314
- Dibs on putting the cuffs
on her when they do.

39:11.349 --> 39:13.351
- Whew.
- All right.

39:14.904 --> 39:19.046
- ♪ Maybe I'm dreaming

39:19.080 --> 39:22.049
- Half day?
- [chuckles] You know me.

39:22.083 --> 39:24.431
Slacker is my middle name.
[elevator bell dings]

39:24.465 --> 39:27.226
♪

39:27.261 --> 39:29.436
After you.

39:29.470 --> 39:31.990
- ♪ I'll rage on

39:32.024 --> 39:35.856
♪ Brave and kind
to my rivals ♪

39:35.890 --> 39:37.236
♪

39:37.271 --> 39:39.307
♪ And maybe I love the way

39:39.342 --> 39:42.828
- You probably saved my life.

39:42.863 --> 39:44.623
- You had him.

39:44.658 --> 39:47.039
- I was upside down
in a footwell,

39:47.074 --> 39:49.145
and he was about to stab me
in the face.

39:49.179 --> 39:51.423
No, I did not have him.

39:51.458 --> 39:53.321
So thank you.

39:54.840 --> 39:56.324
- You're welcome.

39:56.359 --> 40:02.641
♪

40:02.676 --> 40:05.437
- Listen...

40:05.472 --> 40:08.475
I know I ruined everything.

40:08.509 --> 40:10.200
And I know how easy
it would have been

40:10.235 --> 40:12.306
for you to turn on me.
- You don't have to do this.

40:12.340 --> 40:13.859
- Yeah, I do.

40:13.894 --> 40:16.275
You will never know
how much I appreciate

40:16.310 --> 40:19.278
the kindness you've shown me.

40:19.313 --> 40:22.350
And I will spend the rest of
my life trying to pay it back

40:22.385 --> 40:26.009
in whatever
small doses you allow.

40:26.044 --> 40:28.149
♪

40:28.184 --> 40:32.947
- ♪ Maybe I love the way
I can fall on my feet ♪

40:32.982 --> 40:35.674
♪ Keeping my own
kind of bible ♪

40:35.709 --> 40:37.296
- Good night.

40:37.331 --> 40:40.058
- ♪ Maybe I love
how I feel in the wind ♪

40:40.092 --> 40:43.026
♪ I'm the breeze so light

40:43.061 --> 40:45.166
[door buzzes]

40:45.201 --> 40:51.345
♪ I'm light

40:51.379 --> 40:54.831
♪

40:54.866 --> 40:56.488
- That was too easy.

40:56.523 --> 40:58.973
- Cost $100,000.
It better be easy.

40:59.008 --> 41:02.218
♪

41:02.252 --> 41:04.807
[car alarm beeps]
Where can I drop you?

41:04.841 --> 41:07.395
- L.A., baby.

41:07.430 --> 41:09.743
- What have I said
to you about getting shot?

41:09.777 --> 41:10.916
- Okay.

41:10.951 --> 41:12.262
Ow!
[groans]

41:12.297 --> 41:14.713
You said, "Don't get shot."
- Exactly.

41:14.748 --> 41:17.371
It's a simple instruction.
- Yes.

41:17.405 --> 41:20.512
- And to make matters worse,
you got shot in the ass.

41:20.547 --> 41:22.859
- Whoa.
I was shot in the side.

41:22.894 --> 41:24.896
- Of your ass.
- [laughs]

41:24.930 --> 41:27.208
Don't make me laugh.
It hurts my ass.

41:27.243 --> 41:28.589
Okay, changing the subject,

41:28.624 --> 41:30.695
did you take a look at
the adoption stuff I sent you?

41:30.729 --> 41:32.420
- I did.
- And?

41:32.455 --> 41:35.354
- And I compiled
a questionnaire

41:35.389 --> 41:36.701
of all the hoops

41:36.735 --> 41:38.703
we're going to have to jump
through to make sure

41:38.737 --> 41:40.359
that we're on the same page.
- Okay.

41:40.394 --> 41:41.913
- Starting
with the first question--

41:41.947 --> 41:44.709
where are we adopting from,
domestic or foreign?

41:44.743 --> 41:46.642
- Um...
[cell phone rings]

41:46.676 --> 41:47.712
Hold on a moment.

41:47.746 --> 41:49.576
Ow!

41:49.610 --> 41:51.439
Okay.

41:51.474 --> 41:52.786
Sergeant Grey.

41:52.820 --> 41:54.304
Yes, sir?

41:54.339 --> 41:56.583
[tense music]

41:56.617 --> 41:58.723
- What's wrong?

41:58.757 --> 42:01.933
- Oscar and Jason
just escaped from prison.

42:01.967 --> 42:05.212
♪

42:41.628 --> 42:42.974
- Damn it.
